definitions.example: A tree came down and hit me on the head.
The damage sustained in the fire is so great that the whole building will have to come down.
Real estate prices have come down since the peak of the boom.
I can't guess which way the board will come down on the project.
Much wisdom has come down in the form of proverbs.

definitions.definition: To return from an elevated state of consciousness or emotion.
definitions.example: He finally came down from his post-bonus high.

definitions.definition: To graduate from university, especially an Oxbridge university.
